  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What advice would you give yourself if this was your 21 year old self?",
  "response": "If I could give advice to my 21-year-old self, I would suggest the following:\n\n1. **Embrace Change**: Life is unpredictable and filled with surprises. Be open to new experiences and adapt when things don\u2019t go as planned.\n\n2. **Invest in Yourself**: Focus on personal growth, whether through education, skills development, or hobbies. The time and effort you invest in yourself now will pay off later.\n\n3. **Build Strong Relationships**: Surround yourself with supportive and positive people. Networking and forming meaningful connections can open many doors in the future.\n\n4. **Prioritize Mental Health**: Take care of your mental well-being. Don\u2019t hesitate to seek help if you\u2019re feeling overwhelmed. Regular self-care is important.\n\n5. **Financial Literacy**: Start learning about budgeting, saving, and investing. Developing good financial habits early can set you up for long-term stability.\n\n6. **Take Risks**: Don\u2019t be afraid to step outside your comfort zone. Some of the best opportunities arise when you take a leap of faith.\n\n7. **Be Kind and Compassionate**: Treat others with kindness and understanding. You never know what battles others are facing, and a little compassion goes a long way.\n\n8. **Stay Curious**: Keep learning and exploring your interests. Curiosity will lead you to new ideas and paths you might not have considered.\n\n9. **Health is Wealth**: Pay attention to your physical health. Establish good habits now, as they will benefit you in the long run.\n\n10. **Live in the Moment**: While it\u2019s important to plan for the future, don\u2019t forget to enjoy the present. Make memories and appreciate the little things.\n\nUltimately, trust in your journey and be patient with yourself. Growth takes time, and every experience is a valuable lesson.",
